<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="529" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1178.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Sullivan</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-05-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 18, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your May 17. Dominican Government assures me vigorous action has been
                            ordered to prevent deliveries of ammunition to Haitian revolutionists.
                            Similar assurance given to Haitian Minister. General receiver of customs
                            under the command of Dominican Government has ordered revenue cutter to
                            Monte Christi.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>